        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 2:48PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
along a outflow boundary 9 miles north of Holloman Air Force Base,
moving north at 5 to 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tularosa.

This includes Highway 54 in New Mexico near mile marker 81.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
